            "name": "Monster Core pg. 298",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Monster Core",
          "page": 298,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "While a single scorpion is itself a menace, swarms of these vermin can be outright devastating. These skittering droves of death swiftly bring down their prey before devouring everything short of the victim's bones.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
